description: Pure Marine Collagen Peptide is sourced from wild caught deep-sea Atlantic Ocean fish, such as cod, or haddock fish skin. In addition, only the skins of kosher fish are used, NOT scales or bones. Pure Marine Collagen Peptide has been treated with Non-GMO food grade enzymes to break down the collagen molecular size (Dalton weight 2500) for optimum absorption and utilization to the bloodstream. Hydrolyzed collagen type I & III is an incomplete protein. Therefore, take on an empty stomach 30 minutes away from food in the morning or right at bedtime. H.A.95 works in synergy with hydrolyzed collagen type I & III and is the most abundant non-sulfated glycosaminoglycan in the body is Hyaluronic Acid aka (hyaluronan) found in copious amounts throughout the connective, epithelial, and neuro tissues. Glycosaminoglycans (GAGs) or mucopolysaccharides are unbranched polysaccharides (carbohydrate polymers) that consist of repeating disaccharide units. The disaccharide units generally are comprised as a first saccharide unit, one of two modified sugars known as N-acetylgalactosamine or N-acetylglucosamine. The second unit is Uronic acid sugar known as Glucuronic acid, which is one monosaccharide unit in the repeating disaccharide units involved with the formation of glycosaminoglycans. Hyaluronic Acid and Glucuronic Acid are negatively charged molecules with high viscosity and are located primarily on the surface of cells and throughout the extracellular matrix (ECM). H.A.95 naturally consist of 95% natural hyaluronic acid and 46% glucuronic acid. These two amino acid sugars work in synergy and are naturally sourced co-factors that the body will recognize and utilize on a cellular level throughout the extracellular matrix and intercellular spaces. Pure pharmaceutical food grade, not synthetically made in a laboratory out of bacterial fermentation.

description: Horsetail (Equisetum arvense) comes from a unique type of grass plant in the Equisetaceae family, the only family of plants that reproduce using spores rather than seeds. Horsetail is a living fossil, being the only living genus of the entire class Equisetopsida in the world. Equisetopsida dominated the forests of the late Paleozoic era. Horsetail has been used for centuries by indigenous peoples for a variety of uses ranging from sandpaper to folk treatments. The most important thing you should know about horsetail extract is that it contains silica, which is an essential mineral in the human body. Silica helps to keep your bones strong and healthy by helping with the absorption of calcium into your bones.* It also helps with the production of collagen, a protein that keeps your skin elastic and youthful-looking.* Horsetail extract can also help promote hair growth.* Horsetail extract may help strengthen the nails and contribute to nail health.* Lastly, it is also a powerful antioxidant, helping to protect against free radical damage to cells and the body, as well as a diuretic which may contribute to urinary tract health.* Our Horsetail Extract is in powder form and does not contain any fillers, additives or artificial flavors.

features: VITAMINS A, D, AND K2 (AS MK-7): This synergistic blend supports: bone structure, density and integrity; proper bone remodeling; calcium utilization; and cardiovascular function.

VITAMIN A HAS MULTIPLE FUNCTIONS IN THE BODY: It is required for normal development, growth and maintenance of the skeleton throughout life. Vitamin A supports the number and activity of osteoclast cells which break down bone tissue, an ongoing process of skeletal maintenance called bone remodeling. Bone remodeling is a natural way the body removes old or weakened bone tissue in order to make room for new, stronger tissue. This process is critical to fracture repair and retaining bone density.

VITAMIN D3 IS ESSENTIAL FOR MAINTAINING NORMAL CALCIUM METABOLISM: Vitamin D3 is needed for proper bone growth & bone remodeling by osteoblasts and osteoclasts and supports calcium absorption in the gut. Research shows that K2 partners with Vitamin D3 to inhibit the production of osteoclast cells (cells that break down bone) in order to help bone-building osteoblasts catch up to maintain a healthy balance. Vitamin D3 also supports cardiovascular function and blood pressure within normal ranges.

VITAMIN K2 HAS BEEN SHOWN TO SUPPORT NORMAL BONE FORMATION: It is responsible for the carboxylation of specific bone proteins that play a regulatory role in bone metabolism. For example, Vitamin K is required for the activation of osteocalcin, a Vitamin K dependant protein that transports calcium from the blood to form a healthy bone matrix. When Vitamin K2 is deficient or not well used in our bodies, bone structure and function can be compromised.

description: Vitamin K has long been recognized as an important fat soluble vitamin essential for blood coagulation and normal bone mineralization. Several different forms of vitamin K exist, with the primary dietary form being vitamin K1, or phylloquinone, found primarily in green vegetables. Another form of vitamin K known as vitamin K2, or menaquinone, is found in animal products such as meat or eggs, as well as in foods such as cheese and natto, a fermented soy product. While most of the benefits of vitamin K were previously attributed to vitamin K1, recent research has identified important benefits for vitamin K2. Two forms of vitamin K2 also occur and are used in dietary supplements: a natural form (known as MK-7) and a synthetic form (known as MK-4). While both forms have been found to have beneficial effects for bone health, the natural MK-7 form of K2 appears to have several advantages over the synthetic form. For maximum benefit, natural vitamin K2 is supplied in this product.

Thanks to the absence of sufficient carbohydrates and an excess of dietary fat, your liver generates greater quantities of what is known as 'ketone bodies', and this effectively puts your body into a metabolic state known as 'ketosis'. description: Citric Acid Powder is a naturally occurring organic acid found primarily in citrus fruits and other plants. It has become a common food additive due to its sour taste and preservative qualities. This citric acid product is in a crystallized powder form. This powder helps preserve food and perishables and is one of the most common food additives. As a natural preservative, it is used to stop dried foods such as cornmeal and confectionery products such as jelly beans, marshmallows and chewing gum from going bad. In soft drinks like lemonade and cola, it is added to preserve its quality and stops it from going bad.* It is often used as a flavoring agent to add sourness, but it also helps support kidney health.* Citric acid has been shown to help maintain healthy uric acid levels in the blood and urine.* It may also help maintain healthy bone density and a healthy pH level in the body.* Despite being acidic, it acts as an alkalizing agent that helps raise the pH of urine and support digestion.* Citric acid may also help support heart and cardiovascular health.* In addition, it acts as an antioxidant and can help fortify the immune system and support healthy skin.* This product is in powder form. It is pure and does not contain any fillers or additives.
